(1)
The intersection of Worth and Park Streets, at Baxter Street. The view shows Nos. 85 and 87 Park Street, south side, at and adjoining the apex of this triangular plot. No. 87 is a 2 1/2 story frame house, with a brick front. Note the Third Ave., Elevated on the Bowery.

August 16, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, but showing the Worth Street side of buildings. They bear Nos. 171-173. No. 173 being the frame house.

August 16, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.
